                <span class="transition-transform duration-200 group-open:rotate-180 text-neutral-400">
                  <svg class="w-4 h-4" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M19 9l-7 7-7-7"></path></svg>
                </span>
              </summary>
              <div class="mt-3 text-xs sm:text-sm text-neutral-555 dark:text-neutral-400 leading-relaxed pl-8 pr-4 space-y-3">
                <p>
                  Your total monthly payment is often referred to as <strong>PITI</strong>, which stands for Principal, Interest, Taxes, and Insurance. When calculating your affordable monthly budget, our tool factors in:
                </p>
                <ul class="list-disc pl-5 space-y-2">
                  <li><strong>Principal &amp; Interest</strong>: The core amount covering your loan balance and lender fees.</li>
                  <li><strong>Property Taxes &amp; Home Insurance</strong>: Standard escrow costs that vary by local county and provider.</li>
                  <li><strong>HOA Fees &amp; PMI</strong>: Homeowners Association dues and Private Mortgage Insurance (required if your down payment is less than 20% on a conventional loan).</li>
