              <div class="mt-3 text-xs sm:text-sm text-neutral-555 dark:text-neutral-400 leading-relaxed pl-8 pr-4 space-y-3">
                <p>
                  An amortization schedule is a complete table showing your loan repayment progression over time. Early in a 15 or 30-year fixed-rate mortgage, the vast majority of your monthly payment goes toward covering interest expenses. Over time, the math shifts, and a larger portion goes directly toward principal reduction. Our calculator generates both an annual summary and a monthly visual chart to help you track this lifecycle.
